#. <section class="sutta" id="sn1.35"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn1.35:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 1"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 1"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn1.35:0.2"
msgid "4. Satullapakāyikavagga"
msgstr "4. The Satullapa Group"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn1.35:0.3"
msgid "35. Ujjhānasaññisutta"
msgstr "35. Disdain"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.24"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.35:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "sn1.35:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sambahulā ujjhānasaññikā devatāyo abhikkantāya rattiyā "
"abhikkantavaṇṇā kevalakappaṃ jetavanaṃ obhāsetvā yena bhagavā "
"tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā vehāsaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu."
msgstr ""
"Then, late at night, several glorious deities of the Disdainful Group, "
"lighting up the entire Jeta’s Grove, went up to the Buddha, and stood in the "
"air."

msgctxt "sn1.35:1.3"
msgid "Vehāsaṃ ṭhitā kho ekā devatā bhagavato santike imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Standing in the air, one deity recited this verse in the Buddha’s presence:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.35:2.1"
msgid "“Aññathā santamattānaṃ,"
msgstr "“Someone who really is one way,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:2.2"
msgid "aññathā yo pavedaye;"
msgstr "but shows themselves another way,"

# See BB for kitava
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:2.3"
msgid "Nikacca kitavasseva,"
msgstr "is like a cheating gambler"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:2.4"
msgid "bhuttaṃ theyyena tassa taṃ."
msgstr "who enjoys what was gained by theft."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.50"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.35:3.1"
msgid "Yañhi kayirā tañhi vade,"
msgstr "You should only say what you would do;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:3.2"
msgid "yaṃ na kayirā na taṃ vade;"
msgstr "you shouldn’t say what you wouldn’t do."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:3.3"
msgid "Akarontaṃ bhāsamānaṃ,"
msgstr "The wise will recognize"

# BB has two separate devas speaking here, presumably following the comm. But the text clearly indicates that it is a single deva, and the close -ti is only found here.
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:3.4"
msgid "parijānanti paṇḍitā”ti."
msgstr "one who talks without doing.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.35:4.1"
msgid "“Na yidaṃ bhāsitamattena,"
msgstr "“Not just by speaking,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:4.2"
msgid "ekantasavanena vā;"
msgstr "nor solely by listening,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:4.3"
msgid "Anukkamitave sakkā,"
msgstr "are you able to progress"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:4.4"
msgid "yāyaṃ paṭipadā daḷhā;"
msgstr "on this hard path,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:4.5"
msgid "Yāya dhīrā pamuccanti,"
msgstr "by which wise ones practicing absorption"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:4.6"
msgid "jhāyino mārabandhanā."
msgstr "are released from Māra’s bonds."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.35:5.1"
msgid "Na ve dhīrā pakubbanti,"
msgstr "The wise certainly don’t act like that,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:5.2"
msgid "viditvā lokapariyāyaṃ;"
msgstr "for they understand the ways of the world."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:5.3"
msgid "Aññāya nibbutā dhīrā,"
msgstr "The wise are extinguished by understanding,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:5.4"
msgid "tiṇṇā loke visattikan”ti."
msgstr "they’ve crossed over clinging to the world.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.51"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.35:6.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho tā devatāyo pathaviyaṃ patiṭṭhahitvā bhagavato pādesu sirasā "
"nipatitvā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"Then those deities landed on the ground, bowed with their heads at the "
"Buddha’s feet and said:"

#. VAR: yathābālaṃ yathāmūḷhaṃ yathāakusalaṃ → yathābālā yathāmūḷhā yathāakusalā (s1-3, km, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn1.35:6.2"
msgid ""
"“accayo no, bhante, accagamā yathābālaṃ yathāmūḷhaṃ yathāakusalaṃ, yā mayaṃ "
"bhagavantaṃ āsādetabbaṃ amaññimhā."
msgstr ""
"“We have made a mistake, sir. It was foolish, stupid, and unskillful of us "
"to imagine we could attack the Buddha!"

msgctxt "sn1.35:6.3"
msgid ""
"Tāsaṃ no, bhante, bhagavā accayaṃ accayato paṭiggaṇhātu āyatiṃ saṃvarāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Please, sir, accept our mistake for what it is, so we will restrain "
"ourselves in future.”"

msgctxt "sn1.35:6.4"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā sitaṃ pātvākāsi."
msgstr "At that, the Buddha smiled."

msgctxt "sn1.35:6.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho tā devatāyo bhiyyoso mattāya ujjhāyantiyo vehāsaṃ abbhuggañchuṃ."
msgstr "Then those deities, becoming even more disdainful, flew up in the air."

msgctxt "sn1.35:6.6"
msgid "Ekā devatā bhagavato santike imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi:"
msgstr "One deity recited this verse in the Buddha’s presence:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.35:7.1"
msgid "“Accayaṃ desayantīnaṃ,"
msgstr "“If you don’t give your pardon"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:7.2"
msgid "yo ce na paṭigaṇhati;"
msgstr "when a mistake is confessed,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:7.3"
msgid "Kopantaro dosagaru,"
msgstr "with hidden anger and heavy hate,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:7.4"
msgid "sa veraṃ paṭimuñcatī”ti."
msgstr "you’re fastened tight to enmity.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.52"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.35:8.1"
msgid "“Accayo ce na vijjetha,"
msgstr "“If no mistake is found,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: nocidhāpagataṃ → nocīdha apahataṃ (s1-3, km) | nocīdhāpagataṃ (pts1) | no cidhāpagataṃ (pts2) | nocidhāpakataṃ (?)
msgctxt "sn1.35:8.2"
msgid "nocidhāpagataṃ siyā;"
msgstr "if no-one’s gone astray,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:8.3"
msgid "Verāni na ca sammeyyuṃ,"
msgstr "and enmities are settled,"

# the sense of this verse is a little obscure, see BB’s note. I suggest that an a-has been elided from kusala.
#. <br>
#. VAR: kenīdha → tenīdha (bj) | ko nīdha (pts2)
msgctxt "sn1.35:8.4"
msgid "kenīdha kusalo siyā”ti."
msgstr "then who could have been unskillful?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.35:9.1"
msgid "“Kassaccayā na vijjanti,"
msgstr "“Who makes no mistakes?"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:9.2"
msgid "kassa natthi apāgataṃ;"
msgstr "Who doesn’t go astray?"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:9.3"
msgid "Ko na sammohamāpādi,"
msgstr "Who doesn’t fall into confusion?"

#. <br>
#. VAR: ca → ko cā (bj) | kodha (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn1.35:9.4"
msgid "ko ca dhīro sadā sato”ti."
msgstr "Who is the wise one that’s ever mindful?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.25"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.35:10.1"
msgid "“Tathāgatassa buddhassa,"
msgstr "“The Realized One, the Buddha,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:10.2"
msgid "sabbabhūtānukampino;"
msgstr "compassionate for all beings:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:10.3"
msgid "Tassaccayā na vijjanti,"
msgstr "that’s who makes no mistakes,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:10.4"
msgid "tassa natthi apāgataṃ;"
msgstr "and that’s who doesn’t go astray."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:10.5"
msgid "So na sammohamāpādi,"
msgstr "He doesn’t fall into confusion,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: sova → sodha (si, s1-3, km) | so ca (pts1)
msgctxt "sn1.35:10.6"
msgid "sova dhīro sadā satoti."
msgstr "for he’s the wise one, ever mindful."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.53"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.35:11.1"
msgid "Accayaṃ desayantīnaṃ,"
msgstr "If you don’t give your pardon"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:11.2"
msgid "yo ce na paṭigaṇhati;"
msgstr "when a mistake is confessed,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:11.3"
msgid "Kopantaro dosagaru,"
msgstr "with hidden anger and heavy hate,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:11.4"
msgid "sa veraṃ paṭimuñcati;"
msgstr "you’re fastened tight to enmity."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:11.5"
msgid "Taṃ veraṃ nābhinandāmi,"
msgstr "I don’t approve of such enmity,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:11.6"
msgid "paṭiggaṇhāmi voccayan”ti."
msgstr "and so I pardon your mistake.”"
